metadata_description: PoshC2 is a proxy aware C2 framework used to aid penetration testers with red teaming. post-exploitation and Lateral Movement. PoshC2 is primarily written in Python3 and follows a modular format to enable users to add their own modules and tools. allowing an extendible and flexible C2 framework. metadata_description: PoshC2 is a proxy aware C2 framework used to aid penetration testers with red teaming. post-exploitation and Lateral Movement. PoshC2 is primarily written in Python3 and follows a modular format to enable users to add their own modules and tools. allowing an extendible and flexible C2 framework. Out-of-the-box PoshC2 comes PowerShell/C# and Python implants with payloads written in PowerShell v2 and v4. C++ and C# source code. a variety of executables. DLLs and raw shellcode in addition to a Python2 payload. These enable C2 functionality on a wide range of devices and operating systems. including Windows. *nix and OSX.
